author: Lindsay Kramer | lkramer@syracuse.com
title: Former CNY hockey star dominates in Cornell win
text:
Cornell freshman forward Anthony Angello looks like he'll be an early impact player for the Big Red.
Angello, a Manlius native, scored four goals in Cornell's 6-1 win over Laurentian on Sunday.
Angello, 19, was a fifth-round pick by Pittsburgh in the 2014 draft. He posted 19 goals and 16 assists for Omaha of the USHL last season.
Cornell's regular season begins Friday at Niagara.
